articles.title: Yahoo Finance
articles.content: Wall Street stocks shrugged off early weakness Tuesday and joined European bourses in rising on continued hopes the Federal Reserve will cut interest rates next month. Earlier, London, Paris and Frankfurt all pushed higher. US data releases pointed to slower than expected growth of retail sales in September, while producer prices increased in line with expectations.
